node.text:
Are you ready to dance again? Here, famed dancers Melissa Verdecia, Calvin Royal III, Xin Ying, Misty Copeland, Savion Glover, Stella Abrera, Vinson Fraley, Lloyd Knight, Courtney Celeste Spears, Tatiana Desardouin, and Tiler Peck showcase each of their individual style and expression of dance.

Featuring: @mmelifern @calvinroyaliii @xin_ying_dance @mistyonpointe the_savionglover @stellaabreradetsky @heyvinson @lloydknight @bahamaballerina @tatianadesardouin @tilerpeck

Director + Director of Photography: @mr_dume
Stylist: @samiranasr
Producers: @kriceee @imurillo
Assistant Camera: @forthexperience
Editor: @mr_dume
Colorist: @ericaharperdillman
Motion Designer: @annaaaiello
Entertainment Director: @angcutt

node.title: Misty Copeland, Savion Glover & More World-Class Dancers Are Back on Stage

Our August cover star @GigiHadid embarks on her dream cake-baking internship under #CakeBoss's own @BuddyValastro, the prolific baker of cakes best known for his impressive larger-than-life cake designs. Here, Gigi talks cooking and baking with her family on the farm, everything bagel pregnancy cravings, and favorite ‘Cake Boss’ moments.

node.text: “Black leisure is a necessary topic that underscores the threat—and liberation—of mobility in this country,” writes @_MorganJerkins. “Who gets to go where and who gets to do what they want at that particular place has never been equal across the board for people of different races.” During Jim Crow, Black vacationers found joy in Black-owned resorts throughout the United States. At the link in bio, the novelist chases the last glimmers of history in these vital spaces of rest and escape.

The real turning point in Samara Weaving’s (@samweaving) decision to pursue acting came after seeing ‘Pirates of the Caribbean’ at age 12. “I was exported out of this world,” she says. “I was just so filled with curiosity, and I knew I wanted to be a part of whatever just happened to me. I wanted to know how to get an invitation to that party.” For our September issue, the actress talks playing a social media influencer on @9strangershulu, getting starstruck by her castmates (Nicole Kidman, Melissa McCarthy, and Michael Shannon, to name a few), and staying grounded through it all.
